### Define explore() function
Define a function that applies the following methods to the DataFrame: \
     - **.info()**: returns the column names, non-Null counts, and data types for all columns \
     - **.nunique()**: displays the number of unique values in each column \
     - **.apply(pd.unique)**: applies unique method to each of the columns in the DataFrame\
import pyodbc
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
%matplotlib inline
import seaborn as sns
import numpy as np

def explore(df):
    df.info()
    print("============================================\n")
    print(df.nunique())
    print("============================================\n")
    print(df.apply(pd.unique))

