## Vector vs Raster
### Which format to choose?
Raster images (PNG) are pixel based and can lose quality when scaled \
     - Use PNG for images that do not need much scaling (bar/hist charts) \
Vector images (SVG) use mathematical paths, keeping crisp edges regardless of size \
     - Use SVG for images that require more scaling (scatter plots, box plots)
